article.headline: Commodores' Davis named tourney MVP
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Ashley Earley made 9 of 11 shots and
scored 20 points to lead Vanderbilt (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) over Pepperdine 78-46
Tuesday night in the championship game of the Hilton Woodland Hills
Beach Classic.

Dee Davis had 19 points on 6-for-8 shooting for the Commodores
(9-1) and was chosen as the tournament's most valuable player.

Lauren Wenski led Pepperdine (3-8) with 15 points and Jennifer
Lacy had 14.

Abi Ramsey added 14 points for Vanderbilt, and Katy Antony led
the Commodores with seven rebounds and six assists.
